AD ‚ÄòMummy can I go on your phone?‚Äô- times a hundred every day, my #MumLife literally every day haha. ü§¶üèº‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è
.
As some of Darcy‚Äôs friends start having phones, it‚Äôs natural that she wants one too. I‚Äôm happy for DarcyDoodles to use phones for calling or texting (as long as it‚Äôs not strangers and I can check the communications are positive and respectful both ends) but I‚Äôm just not ready for all the big things (stranger danger, website access etc) that come with a full on phone. It‚Äôs fair to say I‚Äôm overly cautious with things like this but I think a lot of us are, right?
.
With all this in mind, I recently started working with Sky Mobile who, in my opinion, have the perfect product for us right now called SPACETALK. It‚Äôs a watch for Darcy linked to an app on MY phone that allows her to call, message, check the weather, use a step counter, torch, GPS tracking and just yanno, tell the time! üí´
.
What I LOVE about it is that I set the contacts she has in there (and can remove), I can set it to school mode (I decide which features work during school hours), I can set the message options (so I can actually supply a list of options to text like, ‚ÄòCraft club is cancelled‚Äô, or, ‚ÄòLove you Mummy!‚Äô), the phone element is all speaker phone so there can be no secret whispered calls and it has no access to websites. I feel safe with this. üíñ
.
I hope this will give Darcy the increased freedom she wants and give her a really good, safer introduction to communicative tech. I also think she‚Äôll just feel cool having a gadget on her ‚åöÔ∏è
.
I honestly think this would make the perfect Christmas gift from a close family member like a Gma & Gdad who often struggle with what to buy (I‚Äôve had some absolute gems from my Gma haha) and you can find it via Sky Mobile online and pay ¬£10 per month or from Dixons and pay ¬£100 upfront and use a Sky Mobile SIM.
.
I‚Äôve popped some more details on my stories! When you were 8, wouldn‚Äôt have just LOVED this? I know I would have haha! #SkySpaceTalk

Wanted to put this post up now because I have some branded content later (it‚Äôs such a cool product- I totally mum-geeked over it ü•∞) so hopefully you‚Äôll enjoy that later too. Two posts in one day eh?!üí´

Hope you‚Äôre all having joy filled days too. If you‚Äôre mum is contactable and you feel able, drop her a line and tell her you love her xxxx

I‚Äôve been feeling quite pressured to do ALL the #festive stuff lately. Social media makes you think everyone is constantly at garden centres seeing Santa or at a stately home seeing the lights or looking like goddesses at Christmas parties! I suddenly felt really sh*t because I haven‚Äôt booked #Santa or baked #mincepies. Anyone relate?üéÑüò´‚ù§Ô∏è
.
For anyone in my boat, here‚Äôs a few things I told myself today:
üéÖüèªInsta is best bits, not daily bits. Can‚Äôt compare your dailies to bests.
üéÖüèªThe greatest present is your presence.
üéÖüèªThere‚Äôs still time! Book something!
.
Tomorrow we‚Äôre doing something I love doing every year, I‚Äôm going to see about finding a Santa to visit and anything else will be a bonus. If all we do is watch Christmas films and snuggle, that‚Äôs fine with me.
.
Give yourself permission to take pressure off and let life happen round you ‚ù§Ô∏èAnyone else just breathe a big sigh of relief? X
